hpnicfAggLinkTable.name: hpnicfAggLinkTable
hpnicfAggLinkTable.description: A table of aggregate link objects.

hpnicfAggLinkNumber.name: hpnicfAggLinkNumber
hpnicfAggLinkNumber.description: The serial number of aggregation group.

hpnicfAggLinkMode.name: hpnicfAggLinkMode
hpnicfAggLinkMode.description: Type of aggregation. manual: Manual aggregation, no LACP. static: Membership specified by user, LACP is used to validate. dynamic: Completely dynamic aggregation detected by LACP.

hpnicfAggLinkPortList.name: hpnicfAggLinkPortList
hpnicfAggLinkPortList.description: List of ports in this link aggregation group, by bridge port number. If the mode of the link aggregation group is manual or static, you can update this list to your hearts content. However, if the link aggregation group is dynamic, the system will maintain it. You are not permitted to set the value of this to all zeroes.

hpnicfAggLinkState.name: hpnicfAggLinkState
hpnicfAggLinkState.description: RowStatus, now support three states: createAndGo, active, destroy.

hpnicfAggPortListSelectedPorts.name: hpnicfAggPortListSelectedPorts
hpnicfAggPortListSelectedPorts.description: A PortList of physical ports that have been selected but not attached to this aggregator. When the bit is set to 1,it means the corresponding port is in the portlist.

hpnicfAggPortListSamePartnerPorts.name: hpnicfAggPortListSamePartnerPorts
hpnicfAggPortListSamePartnerPorts.description: PortList of physical ports that have the same Actor SystemID and partner systemID as this aggregator, but have different actor and partner keys of aggregator.

hpnicfAggPortTable.name: hpnicfAggPortTable
hpnicfAggPortTable.description: A table of aggregate port objects.

hpnicfAggPortIndex.name: hpnicfAggPortIndex
hpnicfAggPortIndex.description: Port ifindex which is according to RFC1213 MIB.

hpnicfAggPortNotAttachedReason.name: hpnicfAggPortNotAttachedReason
hpnicfAggPortNotAttachedReason.description: Reason why this port is selected for an aggregator but not attached, 0: The port is attached to this aggregator. 1: The current number of active ports has reached the upper limit. 2: All aggregation resources are already in-use. 3: The port's configuration is improper for being attached. 4: The port's partner is improper for being attached. 5: The number of current active ports has not reached the lower limit. 6: The port's physical state (down) is improper for being attached. 7: The port is not selected for an aggregator. 8: The port's hardware restriction is improper for being attached. 9: The port's speed is improper for being attached. 10: The port's duplex mode is improper for being attached.

hpnicfAggPortLacpState.name: hpnicfAggPortLacpState
hpnicfAggPortLacpState.description: Control ports' lacp enble or disable.

hpnicfAggPortNotAttachedString.name: hpnicfAggPortNotAttachedString
hpnicfAggPortNotAttachedString.description: The string which interprets this port is selected for an aggregator but not attached.

hpnicfAggResourceAllocationValue.name: hpnicfAggResourceAllocationValue
hpnicfAggResourceAllocationValue.description: The priority value calculated to decide which aggregations have first call on the load-sharing aggregation resources in the hardware. It depends on the aggregation type and total speed.

hpnicfAggSpeedChangedNotification.name: hpnicfAggSpeedChangedNotification
hpnicfAggSpeedChangedNotification.description: This event will be triggered whenever an aggregation changes its speed.

hpnicfAggPortInactiveNotification.name: hpnicfAggPortInactiveNotification
hpnicfAggPortInactiveNotification.description: This event will be triggered whenever any port in aggregator is made inactive.

hpnicfAggPortInactiveNotification2.name: hpnicfAggPortInactiveNotification2
hpnicfAggPortInactiveNotification2.description: This event will be triggered whenever the port in aggregator is made inactive.

hpnicfAggPortActiveNotification.name: hpnicfAggPortActiveNotification
hpnicfAggPortActiveNotification.description: This event will be triggered whenever the port in aggregator is made active.

hpnicfLAGMibCompliance.name: hpnicfLAGMibCompliance
hpnicfLAGMibCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMP entities which implement the Lag MIB.

hpnicfLAGMibObjectGroup.name: hpnicfLAGMibObjectGroup
hpnicfLAGMibObjectGroup.description: The collection of objects which are used to represent LAG objects.

hpnicfLAGMibNotificationGroup.name: hpnicfLAGMibNotificationGroup
hpnicfLAGMibNotificationGroup.description: The collection of objects which are used to represent notifications.
